Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.72,0:02:06.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're absolutely sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.22,0:02:09.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Nyunga Ro Im is a spirit\Nthat belches out clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.96,0:02:12.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and generates water\Nin both Nayug and Sagu?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.07,0:02:21.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.50,0:02:25.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's a good thing I didn't mistake the\Negg for a water spirit and exorcise it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.51,0:02:37.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, the stories told in Yogo\Nabout an evil water demon being slain...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.02,0:02:42.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, their entire official history of\Nthe country itself is all wrong, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.76,0:02:47.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they have their reasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.03,0:02:49.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...what's to become of\Nthe boy who carries the egg?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.53,0:02:51.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Nyunga Ro Chaga...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.77,0:02:54.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right, I'm talking about\Nthe guardian of the spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.70,0:02:57.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Nyunga Ro Chaga...egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.58,0:03:02.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It will do him no real harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.81,0:03:05.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Nyunga Ro Chaga...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.52,0:03:11.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Cruel fate? What do\Nyou mean, "cruel fate"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.16,0:03:21.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Certain death awaits him? What are\Nyou saying will happen to the boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.84,0:03:30.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rarunga?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.97,0:03:34.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that the boy has to\Ndie to protect the egg from him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:37.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly is this Rarunga?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.35,0:03:41.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,An egg-eater?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.06,0:03:51.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! I'm not done talking to you yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.87,0:04:00.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Where is this\N"Land of Feasting" you mentioned?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.70,0:04:03.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why does he have to go there\Non the "spring day of equality"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.77,0:04:05.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How will the egg hatch there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.04,0:04:08.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can leave once you've\Nanswered all my questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.18,0:04:17.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The egg will do what\Nneeds to be done?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.34,0:04:34.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Certain death...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.68,0:04:49.69,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 14\NThe Knot
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.85,0:04:54.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The honored ancestor Torugaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.12,0:04:57.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...having crossed the wild seas and\Nreached the verdant shores of Nayoro...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.96,0:05:02.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...was asked by the Yakoo, the land's\Ninhabitants, to slay a vile water demon...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.83,0:05:06.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that appeared once every\Nhundred years to cause a great drought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.54,0:05:11.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torugaru, the Great Master Star\NReader Nanai, and the Warriors Eight...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.24,0:05:14.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...forced their way deep into\Nthe Misty Blue Mountain range.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.98,0:05:19.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There, in a grove\Nshrouded in dense mist...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.72,0:05:22.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...sat a child next to\Na bubbling spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.42,0:05:25.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The child pointed to the spring\Nand spoke thus to Torugaru...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.96,0:05:30.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Worship me. I rule over\Nall the waters of this land."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.63,0:05:36.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"If you worship me, I shall bestow\Nbountiful harvests to your lands."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.57,0:05:41.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Torugaru was not deceived\Nby the demon's words.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.67,0:05:45.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No sooner did his blade, Star's Heart,\Nslide forth from its sheath...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:51.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...than the child transformed into\Na slimy water demon and attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:05:56.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For three days and nights Torugaru and\Nthe Warriors Eight continued the fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.49,0:05:58.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...until at last they cut off\Nthe water demon's head...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.82,0:06:02.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and let the blue blood from\Nthe stump gush into the spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.83,0:06:08.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At that instant, lightning tore the\Nheavens asunder and struck the spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.27,0:06:15.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Blue light filled the spring, which became\Na gentle rain that nourished the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.94,0:06:20.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Having reclaimed the\Nland's bounty of water...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:23.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Torugaru proclaimed himself\Nmikado, a child of heaven...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.91,0:06:26.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and founded the\NShin-Yogo empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:36.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the official history,\Nthe canonical scripture which...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.49,0:06:40.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...we star readers are required to\Ncommit to memory before any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.06,0:06:45.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To think that it was all a fabrication\Ncreated to rule the country...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.38,0:07:00.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm positive that I killed Karbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.32,0:07:08.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But according to what\Nthat teacher told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.33,0:07:18.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are no blood stains\Nor splatter marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.60,0:07:25.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I fully intended to break\Nmy vow and kill that man, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.94,0:07:31.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if she says I didn't kill him,\NI'm not going to argue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.28,0:07:33.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever happens, happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.46,0:07:48.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Charcoal oil? You don't\Nsee that very often...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.23,0:07:53.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it's spewing that much, these fields\Nwon't be good for farming for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.08,0:08:07.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:10.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mistress Torogai?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.32,0:08:12.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mistress Torogai!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.93,0:08:17.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mistress Torogai! Mistress Torogai!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.37,0:08:29.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is I.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.68,0:08:40.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The master star reader will not\Nreturn until the third bell today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.95,0:08:43.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.39,0:08:45.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please, think nothing of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.49,0:08:49.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since you told us that\NPrince Chagum might still be alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.66,0:08:52.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...our goal has been\Nthe same as yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:55.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.69,0:09:25.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.13,0:09:30.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I went to\Nthe festival that you almost...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.83,0:09:32.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It had nothing to do with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.14,0:09:35.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was my problem to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.08,0:09:41.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.48,0:09:43.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm not injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.51,0:09:46.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, how is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.48,0:09:50.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine too. Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.42,0:09:52.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mistress? You were\Nawake this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.56,0:09:56.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I had been, do you think\NI would have let you treat me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.13,0:10:00.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Disgusting! What is\Nthis horrible stench?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.86,0:10:02.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's charcoal oil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.70,0:10:06.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Charcoal oil? Where in the world\Ndid I get that smell on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.57,0:10:10.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She says you were lying in a pool of\Ncharcoal oil gushing from a rice terrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.34,0:10:11.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.88,0:10:16.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But how could I have\Npossibly survived that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.71,0:10:21.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.\NCould charcoal oil be that thing's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:26.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's still so much in this world\Nthat's beyond my understanding...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.92,0:10:29.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you muttering\Nto yourself about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.19,0:10:31.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please explain so\Nwe can all understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.53,0:10:37.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, weren't you going to\Nthe Knot to question the Water Folk?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.47,0:10:39.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the Knot, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.20,0:10:42.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I learned all sorts of\Nthings from the Water Folk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.04,0:10:45.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Including the fact that\Nyour egg is harmless...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.91,0:10:49.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and that Shin-Yogo's\N"official history" is a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.65,0:10:51.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.41,0:10:56.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We've all been completely taken in\Nby the lies of the official history.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.92,0:10:59.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For some 200 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.83,0:11:07.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... How am I\Nsupposed to put that into words?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.13,0:11:09.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what a pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.10,0:11:16.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know! I have to tell\Nthe others about this too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.71,0:11:19.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave without it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.48,0:11:24.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Am I imagining things?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.85,0:11:32.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave without it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.72,0:11:37.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave without it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.66,0:11:38.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave without what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.89,0:11:42.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mean the knowledge\NI got from the Water Folk?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.33,0:11:45.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave without it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.47,0:11:46.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave without it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:48.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave without it!\NAh, you people must be the Fire Folk!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.84,0:11:52.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought I'd see the real thing!\NThat's the Knot for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.08,0:11:59.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.39,0:12:07.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seems I'll have to carve the information\Ninto a stone to take it with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.14,0:12:25.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have been telling them\Nthat Prince Chagum is alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.84,0:12:29.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the more I read\Nand decipher the epitaphs...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.45,0:12:31.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the more despondent I become.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.22,0:12:38.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"The water demon...depicted in\Nthe official history...of Shin-Yogo..."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.99,0:12:43.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"...is not a demon...\Nthat brings drought."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:49.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Rather, it is a water spirit that bestows...\Nthe blessing of water to this land."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.40,0:12:58.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not knowing the intent of Nanai, the\Nfirst star reader, who had these carved...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.04,0:13:03.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...we star readers have committed\Na terrible crime neglecting to read this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.58,0:13:07.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if it truly is a water spirit\Nthat possessed the prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.65,0:13:12.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...then the spreading sign of the great\Ndrought must be proof of his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.96,0:13:20.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, I must not give up hope yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.60,0:13:22.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The official history was a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:26.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, it is possible\Nthat the prince may still be alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.00,0:13:33.01,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.71,0:13:43.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The world of Nayug has existed\Nback-to-back with our world of Sag...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.85,0:13:48.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The two worlds influence, support,\Nand co-exist with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.82,0:13:51.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To a greater extent\Nthan I ever imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.33,0:13:58.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, boy. Do you know\Nhow caves are formed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:04.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pay attention. Caves are formed\Nby water gradually dissolving away...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.57,0:14:07.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...a layer of comparatively soft earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.54,0:14:11.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That being the case, where does\Nthe water take that dissolved earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.31,0:14:17.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It either seeps into the earth...\Nor perhaps forms a river?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.79,0:14:18.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.70,0:14:29.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I gave them the slip.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.20,0:14:32.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I'd better get out of here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.10,0:14:38.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'm going upwards, but I don't\Nthink the exit is anywhere near here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.14,0:14:40.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.55,0:14:44.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A river?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.15,0:14:48.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I follow the flow of water,\NI can get outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.05,0:14:54.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like the river\Nis right below me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.06,0:14:59.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what this strange soil is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.48,0:15:17.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All this is their dung?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.08,0:15:19.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.68,0:15:26.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, now what? A dead end?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.19,0:16:39.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'm still in one piece...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.45,0:17:00.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! I'm not safe just yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.95,0:17:06.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.56,0:17:09.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.46,0:17:10.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This way...\NThis way?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.43,0:17:14.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't the Fire Folk!\NWho are you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.40,0:17:15.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.86,0:17:18.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And just what do you\Nmean by this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.87,0:17:21.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The way out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.45,0:17:32.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What was that light I saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.35,0:17:38.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I fell for it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.05,0:17:41.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe they\Nlured me in here to eat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.04,0:18:03.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is ridiculous! I haven't\Neven lived half of my days yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.21,0:18:06.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not about to die here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.48,0:18:11.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you're hungry, eat this fella first!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.74,0:18:33.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm reborn into my next life,\NI'll make damn sure I'm born in Nayug!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.03,0:19:00.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.87,0:19:07.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And that's my story.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.98,0:19:16.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, that giant worm led you\Nback here to safety, my mentor?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.35,0:19:21.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, that was something else.\NI was eaten by it, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.42,0:19:25.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Still, it's hard to believe you\Ncame back as part of its dung.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.13,0:19:31.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You hold your tongue! It's not like\Nyou've ever believed in any of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.70,0:19:35.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that something that\Nwants to protect the water spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.24,0:19:38.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...told me where to find\Nthe exit that led back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.47,0:19:42.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Nayug is made up\Nof all sorts, just like Sagu is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.05,0:19:50.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if Torugaru, the founding father,\Ndidn't really slay the water spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.42,0:19:54.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...why would such a story be\Nrecorded in the official history?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.89,0:19:55.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.92,0:19:58.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they wanted to\Nsecure their grip on the country...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.39,0:20:00.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...by putting him on a pedestal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.40,0:20:02.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's probably\Nthe long and short of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.80,0:20:06.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But wouldn't they have considered\Nthat covering up the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.13,0:20:09.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...would be dangerous\Nfor future generations?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.31,0:20:13.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They must have realized\Nthat a new water spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.01,0:20:14.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...would be born\Nevery hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.94,0:20:18.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There might be a record of it\Nleft somewhere inside the palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.81,0:20:24.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but I doubt that anyone in charge\Nthere now knows about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.09,0:20:29.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I used to think...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.56,0:20:33.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it was foolish of the Nyunga Ro Im\Nto lay its egg inside the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.96,0:20:36.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if the people of the palace\Nknew the significance of the egg...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.97,0:20:39.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it would be the safest\Nplace in the world for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.80,0:20:44.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Poor thing. That Nyunga Ro Im\Nmade a bad miscalculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.39,0:20:59.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because it has not vanished...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.42,0:21:01.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because the sign of the great\Ndrought has not vanished...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.82,0:21:04.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I believed it must surely\Nmean that he is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.39,0:21:05.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.96,0:21:09.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why has no one\Never read this until now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.40,0:21:12.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we had known the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.47,0:21:17.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Prince Chagum would not have been\Ntreated so terribly, and he'd still be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.39,0:21:31.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.92,0:21:35.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is not yet time for the\Nmaster star reader to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.18,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.71,0:24:46.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa decides to set out\Non a journey to uncover clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.82,0:24:48.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At around the same time, Shuga is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.19,0:24:52.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time,\N"Untimely Death."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 15\NUntimely Death
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.25,0:24:55.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you leaving, entrusting your\Ngoals to those you leave behind?
